OL,4,CBelfast Council flag dispute
OL,6,FAmid unionist objections, a call-in
OL,7,Fmechanism was triggered to scrutinise
OL,8,Fthe legitimacy of the decision.
OL,10,FUnder the procedure a 15% minority of
OL,11,Fcouncillors can request a
OL,12,Freconsideration which involves seeking
OL,13,Flegal opinion on any possible adverse
OL,14,Fcommunity impact.
OL,16,FIf those concerns are assessed as
OL,17,Fbeing valid, an 80% super majority may
OL,18,Fbe required in a call-in for the
OL,19,Foriginal motion to be voted in again.
