OL,6,FShe was also said to regard the
OL,7,Fdecision to fly the Palestinian flag
OL,8,Fas a further attack on unionist values
OL,9,Fand offensive to the city's Jewish
OL,10,Fcommunity.
OL,12,FAt an earlier stage in the case the
OL,13,FCouncil accepted that legal opinion on
OL,14,Fthe merits of a call-in requisition
OL,15,Fshould not be treated as determinative.
OL,17,FBut Mr Larkin claimed newly "cobbled
OL,18,Ftogether" standing order arrangements
OL,19,Fhave arguably made the situation worse.
