OL,6,FA simple majority of councillors will
OL,7,Fnow determine whether any decision
OL,8,Fcalled-in for reconsideration should
OL,9,Fbe subjected to the qualified voting
OL,10,Fprotections, the court heard.
OL,12,FThe barrister contended: "(This)
OL,13,Fplainly and egregiously defies the
OL,14,Fstatutory scheme and subjects the
OL,15,Fminority safeguard to a majority veto."
OL,17,FMr Justice McLaughlin was told that a
OL,18,Fcouncil clerk must determine that a
OL,19,Frequisition is valid before a super-
OL,20,Fmajority vote is required to pass
OL,21,Fpotentially divisive motions.
